parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: I live in the village of Ñangali.

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: One of my children was malnourished,

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: so I went to the medical centre to get food,

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: I went to ask them for food

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: the nurses from Ñangali’s medical centre,

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: ‘We will give you the food but only if you go and get yourself sterilised.

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: If you don’t we won’t give you any food

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: because you all have too many children,

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: and don’t want to be sterilised.

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: And I got to the hospital and I was the last one there,

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: I got there a bit late,

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: On one side there was a man who was getting a vasectomy,

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: They said: ‘Come in. Are you here to be sterilised?’

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: and I felt embarrassed with the man there, because he was naked,

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: and I didn’t want to do it anymore.

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: They put me on the bed

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: and four of them held me down.

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: Two held my arms down and two held my legs,

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: so they could give me the injection,

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: and I don’t remember any more.
